In this press briefing, White House Press Secretary Jay Carney makes several announcements. He mentions that President Obama's speech at the Planned Parenthood National Conference has been rescheduled to allow him to spend more time with those affected by the explosion in West Texas. Carney also reads a statement from the President on the confirmation of Sylvia Mathews Burwell as the Director of the Office of Management and Budget. He discusses the investigation into the Boston bombing, saying that a comprehensive investigation is needed to answer all the questions about the attack. Carney also discusses the sequester, saying that the law does not allow for flexibility in the FAA budget and that Congress needs to take action to mitigate the impact of the sequester. He also discusses the budget, immigration reform, and cyber security. Finally, Carney addresses questions about the diversity lottery, gun control, Fisker Automotive, and the Benghazi attack.